parameters.formDescription: Enter the Apollo personal email list to build your email list with customized email openers.

values.content:
=You are an AI agent that generates short, warm icebreakers for cold emails.  
Each icebreaker must feel personal and grounded in the recipient’s background (title, company, city, industry, or brand keywords).  
The tone should be friendly, conversational, and not salesy.  

### Rules
- Output must ALWAYS be valid JSON with this structure:  
  { "id": "{{ $json.id }}", "icebreaker": "Hey [first_name],\n\n[Sentence 1]. [Sentence 2]" }  

- Constraints:  
  • Max length: 300 characters  
  • Begin with recipient’s first name  
  • Reference ONE specific detail (title, company, city, industry, or keyword)  
  • Simplify long company names for natural flow  
  • No emojis, hashtags, links, or formal sign-offs  

### Fallback Strategy
- If no strong data point is available, reference the person’s **industry** or **headline**.  
- If still nothing, create a neutral but curious opener (e.g. “Hey [first_name], came across your work and it stood out. Wanted to run something by you.”).  

### SOP
1. Extract the most specific & personal field available in priority order:  
   title → organization_name → city → industry → brand keywords → headline  
2. Write a natural 2-sentence message:  
   Sentence 1 = Personalized observation.  
   Sentence 2 = Soft prompt (“Was hoping to run something by you” / “Wanted to get your take on something”).  
3. Format exactly as:  
   { "id": "{{ $json.id }}", "icebreaker": "Hey {{ $json.fields.f_name }},\n\n[Sentence 1]. [Sentence 2]" }

=Instructions:  
- Start with "Hey {{ $json.f_name }},"  
- Use one specific detail (title, organization, city, industry, or brand keyword).  
- Write in two short sentences.  
- Keep it warm, casual, and under 300 characters.  
- End with a soft opener (e.g. “Was hoping to run something by you”).  
- Output ONLY valid JSON in this format:  

{  
  "id": "{{ $json.id }}",  
  "icebreaker": "Hey {{ $json.f_name }},\n\n[Sentence 1]. [Sentence 2]"  
}

parameters.content:
Manual Trigger (Test Mode)

Temporary trigger to run workflow manually for testing.

In production, replace with Form Submission Trigger.

Set Apollo Body (JS Code)

Defines search parameters based on selected segment (Manufacturers, Ecommerce, Traders, Fintech, NGO).

Outputs apolloBody for API call.

Apollo API Request (People Search)

Calls Apollo Mixed People Search API with parameters.

Fetches candidate leads (people + partial org data).

Split Out (Array → Items)

Splits single array response into individual items for easier mapping.

Loop + Extract IDs (JS Code)

Collects person IDs in batches of 10.

Prepares them for Apollo Bulk Match API.

Apollo People Bulk Match

Retrieves verified emails & enriched contact info for each batch of people.

Split Out Matches
Breaks down bulk API response into individual persons.

Organization Details Fetch

Calls Apollo/Org API for enriched org details.

Runs parallel with people data.

Merge Node (People + Organization)

Combines person info + organization info.

Produces unified lead dataset.

Split Out Matches
Breaks down bulk API response into individual organization.

Limit Node (Testing)

Restricts results (e.g., 5 leads) during testing to save tokens.

Loop Rows (Google Sheet)

Iterates over each row to prepare Icebreaker individually.

OpenAI Node (Icebreaker Generator)

System + User prompts create short, personal outreach notes.

Uses title, org, city, keywords, etc.

> **Manual Trigger (Test Mode)**  
> Temporary trigger to run workflow manually for testing.  
> In production, replace with Form Submission Trigger.

---

> **Set Apollo Body (JS Code)**  
> Defines search parameters based on selected segment (Manufacturers, Ecommerce, Traders, Fintech, NGO).  
> Outputs `apolloBody` for API call.

---

> **Apollo API Request (People Search)**  
> Calls Apollo Mixed People Search API with parameters.  
> Fetches candidate leads (people + partial org data).

---


> **Split Out (Array → Items)**  
> Splits single array response into individual items for easier mapping.

---


> **Loop + Extract IDs (JS Code)**  
> Collects person IDs in batches of 10.  
> Prepares them for Apollo Bulk Match API.

---


> **Apollo People Bulk Match**  
> Retrieves verified emails & enriched contact info for each batch of people.

---

> **Split Out Matches (People)**  
> Breaks down bulk API response into individual persons.

---


> **Organization Details Fetch**  
> Calls Apollo Org API for enriched org details.  
> Runs parallel with people data.

---


> **Merge Node (People + Organization)**  
> Combines person info + organization info.  
> Produces unified lead dataset.

---


> **Split Out Matches (Organizations)**  
> Breaks down bulk API response into individual organizations.

---


> **Limit Node (Testing)**  
> Restricts results (e.g., 5 leads) during testing to save tokens.

---


> **Loop Rows (Google Sheet / Airtable)**  
> Iterates over each row to prepare Icebreaker individually.

---


> **OpenAI Node (Icebreaker Generator)**  
> System + User prompts create short, personal outreach notes.  
> Uses title, org, city, keywords, etc.

---



> # Lead Generation Flow Summary  
> This workflow automates the entire cold outreach preparation process:
>
> - **Data Sourcing:** Apollo People Search API → targeted contacts.  
> - **Enrichment:** Apollo Bulk Match + Org endpoints → verified emails, LinkedIn, org info.  
> - **Batch Processing:** Splits leads into batches to respect API limits.  
> - **Storage:** Logs all leads in Airtable (centralized tracking).  
> - **Personalization:** OpenAI generates short, warm icebreakers for each lead.  
> - **CRM Sync:** Pushes data into CRM (Pipedrive/Airtable).  
>
>  Outcome: Sales team gets ready-to-use leads + enriched data + contextual icebreakers → saves research time & boosts reply rates.

organizations.name: DPO Pay by Network
organizations.raw_address: rose avenue, avenue 5 building, 2nd floor, nairobi, nairobi 01000, ke
organizations.short_description:
DPO Pay by Network is a prominent payment service provider based in Nairobi, Kenya. Founded in 2006, the company offers secure, multi-currency payment solutions for businesses ranging from small and medium enterprises to large global corporations. Acquired by Network International in 2020, DPO Pay by Network has become Africa’s largest and fastest-growing payment gateway, focusing on scalability and fraud prevention.

The company provides a range of services, including a payment gateway that supports credit and debit card transactions, mobile money, and cross-border payments. It also features multi-currency support and invoicing tools that allow businesses to generate instant payment links. DPO Pay by Network emphasizes security with 24/7 fraud monitoring and holds PCI DSS Level 1 certification and GDPR compliance, ensuring data protection for its users. The platform serves various sectors, including e-commerce, telecom, and financial services, and is known for its localized payment solutions tailored to the African market.

organizations.name: Mercuryo
organizations.short_description:
Mercuryo is a global payments ecosystem that harmonizes cryptocurrency and fiat solutions, enabling businesses to utilize cryptocurrency for cross-border transactions. Founded in 2018, the company aims to simplify crypto-powered payments, helping businesses operate as global entities. It serves over 250 clients, including notable names in decentralized finance (DeFi) and web3.

The company offers a range of services, including on-/off-ramp solutions for fiat-to-crypto conversions, customizable co-branded crypto debit cards, and API/SDK integration for embedding payment solutions into applications. Mercuryo supports multiple blockchains and provides tailored solutions for various use cases, such as wallets, decentralized exchanges (DEXs), NFT platforms, and yield protocols. Collaborating with industry leaders like MetaMask and Trust Wallet, Mercuryo focuses on long-term innovation and user-centric design, employing over 200 professionals worldwide to enhance its offerings and market presence.

organizations.name: SuperSim
organizations.raw_address: 5955 avenida nove de julho, são paulo, state of são paulo, brazil
organizations.short_description:
SuperSim is a fintech company based in São Paulo, Brazil, founded in 2019. The company specializes in providing microcredit solutions aimed at enhancing financial inclusion for the working-class population. With a team of 201–500 employees, SuperSim operates across South America, Europe, and North America. The company has successfully raised $5 million in Series A funding, with plans to capture a significant share of Brazil’s non-prime credit market.

SuperSim offers tech-enabled microcredit solutions that help non-prime borrowers build creditworthiness through small, short-term loans. Their services focus on enabling customers to establish repayment histories over 24–36 months, facilitating their transition to prime credit products. The company employs a scalable lending infrastructure and data-driven risk assessment to evaluate borrowers effectively. SuperSim's mission is centered on sustainable financial inclusion, aiming to help customers improve their financial standing through consistent repayment behavior.

organizations.name: iugu
organizations.raw_address: avenida das nações unidas 12495, 16° e 17° andar, são paulo, são paulo 04578-000, br
organizations.short_description:
iugu is a Brazilian fintech company founded in 2012 and based in Brooklin, São Paulo. The company focuses on financial automation solutions, signature management, and marketplace services, aiming to simplify and scale financial operations for digital businesses. iugu's platform automates billing processes, manages recurring payments, and facilitates payment splitting, enhancing efficiency for its clients.

The company offers a range of services, including iugu Cobrança for billing automation, iugu Recorrência for recurring payments, and iugu Split for payment splitting. Additionally, iugu provides Banking as a Service (BaaS), allowing clients to manage their financial operations effectively. With over 130,000 active accounts, iugu has gained significant investment from major financial institutions, including Goldman Sachs, and is licensed by the Banco Central do Brasil, ensuring compliance and security in its operations. The company values the integration of technology with human connection, aiming to deliver tailored financial solutions that meet the diverse needs of its clients.

organizations.name: Verto
organizations.raw_address: 1 finsbury avenue, london, england ec2m 2pa, gb
organizations.short_description:
Verto is a global financial technology company that specializes in cross-border payments and foreign exchange solutions for businesses. Founded in 2017 and headquartered in London, UK, Verto focuses on simplifying transactions, particularly in emerging markets like Africa. The company is backed by Y Combinator and aims to provide robust infrastructure for multi-currency conversions, payments, and banking services.

Verto offers a range of services, including cross-border payments in over 200 countries and 49 currencies, FX and treasury management tools, and multi-currency accounts. Their API integration allows for seamless connections with invoice payments and expense management systems. Verto is regulated by the UK's Financial Conduct Authority, ensuring compliance and safeguarding customer funds. With a diverse client base of over 1,000 businesses, Verto is dedicated to reducing fees and friction in cross-border payments, enhancing financial accessibility for companies in developing economies.

organizations.name: finzly
organizations.raw_address: finzly inc., 2815 coliseum centre dr., suite 240, charlotte, north carolina 28217, united states, charlotte, north carolina 28217, us
organizations.short_description:
Finzly is a financial technology company based in Charlotte, North Carolina, founded in 2012. Originally named SwapsTech, the company rebranded to Finzly and has raised $10.05 million in funding as of October 2023. It focuses on modernizing banking infrastructure with API-first, cloud-native solutions for financial institutions.

Finzly offers a range of banking solutions, including a core-independent platform for real-time payments, API-driven embedded banking services, compliance automation tools, and customizable digital banking experiences. The platform supports institutions in adapting to customer needs through composable workflows and promotes interoperability with a network of fintech partners. Finzly primarily serves banks, credit unions, and financial institutions looking to enhance their services and compete effectively in the market. The company has experienced significant growth, doubling its revenue in 2023 and receiving over 20 industry awards for its innovative solutions.

organizations.name: CSC Generation
organizations.raw_address: 24 w randolph st, chicago, illinois, united states
organizations.short_description:
CSC Generation is a technology platform based in Merrillville, Indiana, that specializes in acquiring and transforming retail and e-commerce companies. Founded in 2016, the company focuses on revitalizing struggling brands through data-driven strategies and operational improvements. It often acquires companies in distress, particularly in the home décor and lifestyle sectors, and restructures them for profitability.

The company operates a portfolio of brands, including DirectBuy, Z Gallerie, One Kings Lane, Sur La Table, and Home Consignment Center. CSC Generation enhances these brands by implementing digital transformation strategies, optimizing e-commerce operations, and providing centralized support services like supply chain management and customer experience enhancements. Its approach emphasizes cross-functional expertise in marketing, product development, and engineering to drive growth and modernize operations. Notable investors include Khosla Ventures and Panasonic, highlighting its collaborative approach to brand turnaround.

organizations.raw_address: 33, rue du louvre, paris, île-de-france 75002, fr
organizations.short_description:
Fintecture is a French financial technology company founded in 2017 and based in Saint-Mande. It is regulated by the Banque de France and the ACPR, operating as a payment institution that specializes in digitalizing bank transfers for businesses. The company raised €26 million in a Series A funding round in 2022, bringing its total funding to €32 million. In 2023, Fintecture was recognized as Fintech of the Year by AGEFI.

Fintecture provides a range of payment solutions aimed at enhancing financial operations. Its offerings include Immediate Transfer for real-time bank transfers, Smart Transfer for automated payment routing, Verified Disbursement for secure fund distribution, and Buy Now, Pay Later (BNPL) options for B2B transactions. The company also supports multi-channel integration, allowing for seamless online, in-store, and remote payment solutions. With a focus on e-commerce businesses and financial institutions, Fintecture aims to optimize cash management and improve customer retention through flexible payment options.

organizations.name: Yuno
organizations.raw_address: new york, new york, united states
organizations.short_description:
Yuno is a global payment orchestration platform founded in 2021 and headquartered in New York, United States. The company aims to simplify payment operations for businesses, enhance revenue, and support global expansion. With a workforce of 1,001 to 5,000 employees, Yuno operates in the financial services industry.

Yuno offers a comprehensive payments orchestration solution that connects businesses to over 1,000 global payment methods through a single API integration. Its platform features smart routing technology, which optimizes transaction flow to increase acceptance rates and reduce processing costs. Additionally, Yuno provides fraud prevention services and data analytics tools to help clients track payment metrics and improve their strategies. The company serves notable clients, including McDonald's, Rappi, and Avianca, showcasing its effectiveness in enhancing payment processes and security.

organizations.short_description:
PayTabs Global is a fintech company founded in 2014 by Abdulaziz Al Jouf in Saudi Arabia. It focuses on providing payment infrastructure solutions for small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs) in the MENA region. With headquarters in Saudi Arabia and offices in the UAE, Jordan, Türkiye, and Egypt, PayTabs aims to enhance financial inclusion and digital commerce through secure and scalable payment solutions.

The company offers a range of services, including a unified payment orchestration platform for omni-channel transactions, the PT Touch soft POS solution that turns smartphones into merchant terminals, and tailored B2B payment processing for various sectors such as hospitality and education. PayTabs has also expanded its capabilities by acquiring the social commerce platform Paymes in 2022. The company emphasizes security with advanced fraud detection and compliance protocols, ensuring safe transactions for its clients, which include SMEs, enterprises, and financial institutions across the region.
